<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-07-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-07-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="427" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d427">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.93/191</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Coolidge</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Superior, Wis.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-07-12"><hi rend="italic">July 12,
                                1928</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received July 16.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I approve the program
                            which you set out in your letter of July 11th regarding the matter of
                            the treaty negotiations with China.</p>
                        <p>Very truly yours,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Calvin Coolidge</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>